{"id":31716,"date":"2019-06-02T15:53:15","date_gmt":"2019-06-02T11:53:15","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=31716"},"modified":"2020-12-19T19:14:41","modified_gmt":"2020-12-19T15:14:41","slug":"istighfar-salat-for-tawbah","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/06\/02\/istighfar-salat-for-tawbah\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Istighfar: Praying for repentance after committing a sin"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abu Bakr reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>No man commits a sin, then purifies himself in ablution, then prays, and then asks Allah for forgiveness, but that Allah will forgive him<\/strong>.\u201d Then, the Prophet recited this verse, \u201c<strong>Those who, if they behave immorally or wrong themselves, they remember Allah and seek forgiveness for their sins. Who forgives sins besides Allah? And they do not insist on what they have done, while they know better<\/strong>.\u201d (3:135)<\/p>\n<p>Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 406<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Al-Albani<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u0646 \u0623\u0628\u064a \u0628\u0643\u0631 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0646\u064e\u0651\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0650\u0651 \u0635\u0644\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0639\u0644\u064a\u0647 \u0648\u0633\u0644\u0645 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e <strong>\u0645\u064e\u0627 \u0645\u0650\u0646\u0652 \u0631\u064e\u062c\u064f\u0644\u064d \u064a\u064f\u0630\u0652\u0646\u0650\u0628\u064f \u0630\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0628\u064b\u0627 \u062b\u064f\u0645\u0651\u064e \u064a\u064e\u0642\u064f\u0648\u0645\u064f \u0641\u064e\u064a\u064e\u062a\u064e\u0637\u064e\u0647\u0651\u064e\u0631\u064f \u062b\u064f\u0645\u0651\u064e \u064a\u064f\u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u0650\u064a \u062b\u064f\u0645\u0651\u064e \u064a\u064e\u0633\u0652\u062a\u064e\u063a\u0652\u0641\u0650\u0631\u064f \u0627